Hey it’s the new year! I’m late, I know… I spent the start of the year in Mexico City. Mostly in a holding pattern of exploring, eating, sitting in parks, and thinking about making art. In my final week, I worked on these special pieces for a venue opening later this year. The building is from 1921, and the history was tangible in the space. I was given lots of freedom to try new things here, and that’s what I did! I see and feel big shifts this year…am I ready? Maybe. Will I make art through it all? Yes. 
Thank you all for still being here through this evolution. It means a whole lot. 2023 LFG. Lovely photos by @ale__kelly

*FUN ANNOUNCEMENT!*
I am having a solo showing of my new work at a ten day residency/pop up @whitmanwalker this JUNE. 
.
“EMBODIED” is about a topic deeply personal, but I think one others can relate to.
I suffered for nearly a decade from chronic pain that led me on a healing journey that changed the course of my life. I have only now been able to begin reflecting and processing this chapter, and understanding the gifts it has given me in where I am today, and where I want to go from here. The forms and figures in this show are a celebration of the body, which is a reflection of my own relationship with my physical self. There is so much more I can say on this…but will leave it here for now. 
Art is such a part of my healing - and always will be. It’s my ultimate language, my expression to the world. Sometimes it’s hard to describe, but it’s a way I can understand myself. 

I can’t wait to show you these new pieces. There will be brand new sculptures, paintings and prints. There will be color! And joy. A true celebration of self. 

Thank you all for being here. It really means a lot. I hope to see you in June :D

At least 417 Anti LGBTQ+ bills have been introduced in state legislatures across the US this year alone. From banning drag, to gender affirming care, these initiatives undermine public safety, create a culture of fear based not based in reality, and have critical consequences across all generations. 
Since Roe V Wade was overturned, the fight for reproductive justice has only gotten more tough. Red states continue to pass strict abortion bans that threaten the safety of anyone who has the opportunity to become pregnant. 
Yes, the reality of the political climate can feel grim, but we have to remember and protect the rights we still have, and fight to regain what has been taken away! 
Abortion is still accessible in Washington, DC. The queer community is vibrant and alive here. Drag goes on! We are here to celebrate the accessibility in our nations capital, and to put a stake in reminding other who come here - what DC is all about. 
“Stick It! A Sticker extravaganza” Is a moment to make your voice heard. The public streets are a great place to express yourself. Join us in making stickers, and putting them up…everywhere! 
We want to spread radical LOVE, JOY, and ACCEPTANCE. These stickers may be small, but these acts of reclaiming space with these messages is BIG. 
Hope to see you there!
IT WOULD BE A HUGE HELP if you RSVP to this free event. Link in my BIO 👍

“Twisting Cube” Steel Table. Collaboration with @jordanhamlettsanders 💓
The figures in this piece are from drawings I did of twisted yoga poses. I trained in Ashtanga a loong time ago and explored deeper into yoga and it’s philosophy. It was an important ingredient of healing my body. I especially enjoy twisted poses. I learned how these shapes are beneficial for our bodies to release release toxins and keep mobility in the spine🕺🏻 Enshrining them in a solid steel table seemed appropriate 🙃…. Never made anything like this!

Three vases, in collaboration with @hollowworkceramics are still available at “EMBODIED” - the exhibition has been EXTENDED THROUGH THIS WEEK! It’s open Tues-Thursday 4-8pm. 1701 14th st NW.

Over the past four month, I have had the pleasure to work with four amazing printmakers to expand their skills, learn from mentors in the field, and prepare for a culminating exhibition that opens this weekend! This show explores the relationship we hold with our past, to better understand the present and allow for a unique and creative vision of our future. We must know one, to know the other. Please join us for the opening reception SAT JULY 8, 2-5pm - or for anytime the show is up through August 19th 😎 Thank you @transformerdc for creating this awesome opportunity for artists in DC!

I am taking my annual “big break” this month. This consists of lots of time alone, time away from my art, and a healthy dose of nature spaces. I try to literally downshift into a lower gear. Move slower, notice more, and just BE more. 
This doesn't come easy to me! But it's a consistent practice I have been embracing in recent years. This rest allows me to listen - to my body, to my mind, to what feels good and doesn't as I reflect, process and plan for what’s next. 

My “Embodied” show was a huge highlight. I love sharing the work that is my passion to create - I find it such a beautiful part of the art making process. These pieces were a reflection of the healing journey through deep connection with the body. It was personal, and profound. 

I really would not be here without the consistent support of the DC community. Thats a fact. 
From the deepest part of myself, thank you for coming out to the show. For supporting my work, for collecting my work, for your kind words, your critiques, your questions, your reflections. I listened to it all, and am sitting with it now. 

Thank you for the photos #1,2,3,5 by @mariahmirandaphoto #4 by @yanishootsraw

Studio Sunday…zoning out and carving. 
Still feeling the transition from the mountains, trying to be easy on myself as my mind and body shift back into work mode. 
My anxiety has been like OH HI HELLO since I’ve been back with a full schedule/traffic/news etc. 
I’m remembering that this is just a moment in time, and things will continue to shift/change/evolve and I will settle in. In the meantime, a quiet afternoon making this flower print with a good podcast was pretty dang nice. 
What do you do to find those spaces of calm amidst the (sometimes) chaos? 
#linoprint #linoblock
